\end_inset

) that a Stern-Gerlach experiment could not succeed in establishing the
 spin of an unbound electron because the Lorentz force would blur the detected
 pattern.
 This example illustrates the case of a fundamental physical limitation
 that not even infinite resources could mitigate.
